LET (var)=[(expression)|(string)|(value)]
 assign a value to a variable

OPTIONS:
 (var)        = numeric variable name (A), or string variable name (A$)
 (expression) = either a string expression or a numeric expression
 (string)     = a string of text
 (value)      = an integer or decimal value

EXAMPLES:
 LET total$="total lines: "+lines+" in "+file$
 LET a$="some text"
 LET kbytes=bytes*8
 LET y=23

RELATED:
 DIM,PRINT

